I’ve been having a blast in Singapore! It’s so special to be in office working with the @bandlab team IRL and connecting with all the other amazing folks across Caldecott Music Group!

I’m incredibly inspired by how driven and passionate everyone is, and that extends to the BandLab community. In all my time I’ve never seen artists and fans have such affection toward the software they use and create identity around it. It’s a testament to what can happen when you provide tools that give the power of music making to everyone, without limit or boundaries.

I truly believe that what’s being built here is the future of music. IYKYK.

It’s hard to believe it’s only been two months and this journey is just beginning. Feeling grateful, energized, and HOT (the humidity in Singapore is no joke y’all).

EAT ALL THE THINGS. If you don’t eat your way through Singapore you’re missing out. 🤤🍲 Except durian. Durian took years off my life. 😩

1. Adorable bao
2. Barbecued stingray in chili paste
3. Char siu, roast duck, wonton noodles, gai lan
4. Ang ku kueh
5. Chili crab, salted egg chicken, sautéed deer
6. Chicken congee with pork floss
7. Spiced milk tea with saffron
8. Mutton biryani, mee goreng, martabak 
9. Durian 🤢

This is a story about @noahyoo__ . Back in 2018, he was a brilliant writer for Pitchfork who caught my eye with smart, insightful pieces. I decided we HAD to be friends so I DMed him on Twitter, and he was kind enough to respond.

We stayed in touch and instantly became friends when we met a year later in 2019.

Fast forward to 2021, when I needed to expand my team at Output. As I thought about who would be the perfect fit for the job, only one name came to mind: Noah.

To my delight, Noah was excited about the opportunity and said yes.

Working with Noah was a joy. He energized everyone. He made us laugh. He constantly amazed us all with his depth of knowledge and absolute passion for making music.

Then one day about a year ago, his life changed.

Out of the blue, a song by his band @wearecafune called "Tek It" went viral on TikTok. It absolutely exploded over a matter of days.

He couldn’t believe it was actually happening. I remember him looking at the Shazam data and saying, “I think something’s broken.”

It wasn’t broken though. It was the real deal, and within weeks his band signed with Elektra. It all happened so fast, and when Noah sent in his resignation letter, I was proud. I knew he was nervous, but he was also ready to make a leap of faith.

Now, in less than a year, Cafuné has toured with @chvrches, gone platinum, and is on their own headlining tour!

Last week, they performed a sold-out show in Chicago at Schubas and I got to watch Noah the writer, who became Noah my friend, who became Noah my coworker, now become Noah the rockstar.

He was so at home on stage! The crowd knew every song! People stayed for an hour afterward to take photos!

Once everything had died down, we made a beeline for each other and fell into the longest hug ever. I felt my heart explode at that moment for what he’s been able to accomplish.

Truly, there’s nothing better than watching someone you cherish in life excel in their craft, especially when you support and encourage them along the way.

It’s just the beginning, Noah.

I can’t wait to see what new heights you continue to achieve. Remember to sleep, enjoy the journey, and get a power inverter for the Sprinter.

Hey, it’s me. And I’d like to ask you to read this. ♥️

The @recordingacademy At-Large Trustee election is now open and I’m on the ballot. If you’re a member, your vote would mean the world.

I’m pretty awful when it comes to talking about myself but here goes.

I got roped into Academy service many years back, knowing that women, dance music, DJs, female engineers, and young producers were underrepresented. I wanted to be a part of changing that. Shortly after becoming involved with the Chicago board, I organized a dinner with local dance acts @golfclapdet @karstensollors @genefarris @johnsummit @yehme2 and more (scroll to the last pic for our baby faces!). Many of the people in that photo not only went on to become members, but elected representatives on the board!

As I did the work, I uncovered so many things I loved about service, from initiatives with @musicares to national committees to watching musical collaborations bloom within our own Board that would have never happened otherwise.

I’ve been lucky enough to not only give my time to incredible work at the Academy, but also with organizations like @girlsrockchicago, @campspinoff, and @redbullmusic, mentoring young aspiring producers and DJs.

I’ve also been in the fortunate position to advise and educate the music industry at the highest levels on its most pressing issues, particularly artificial intelligence and copyright reform. If you want someone deeply knowledgeable about AI to advocate for musicians, I’m your person.

I’ve seen what can happen when people from your community stand up for you, ask for your voice to be heard, and say they want you at the table. When you extend a hand in earnest, people tend to take it. And that’s what I’d like to do as Trustee - be that extended hand as I have been so many times before.

As Frankie Knuckles once said: I am definitely in the right place doing the right thing. These are the rewards. ♥️
You do not need anybody’s permission to lead a creative life 🎶💕🪩💫

Honored to have moderated a panel for the city of Chicago about preserving the legendary Warehouse nightclub! 🏢✨ This iconic venue holds a special place in music history as the birthplace of house music, and the collective movement to save it showcased the raw power of community organizing.

Big news: The Warehouse just earned landmark status! 🎉 Thanks to 14,000+ signatures, impassioned testimonies, and the relentless efforts of Preservation Chicago, this sacred space will now stand for generations to come.

This milestone celebrates the unwavering love for house music and its profound cultural heritage. The Warehouse isn't just bricks and mortar—it's a symbol of artistic liberation, inclusivity, and the power to ignite souls. It was a home for the LGBTQ+, Black, and Latino Chicagoans who created this genre that has transcended borders and touched hearts worldwide.

As a passionate advocate for house music, I feel privileged to be part of the conversation to continue preserving Chicago's rich musical heritage. House music all night long 💕✌️♥️

Counting down the days until I take the stage at @walliforniamusictech where I'll be speaking about innovating our way to a more diverse music industry. 🎶✨

I believe in the power of tech to lower barriers and create more equitable creative spaces. I was able to benefit from it myself growing up - my parents bought me Logic Pro one year for Christmas and it meant I could learn how to make tracks without stepping foot in a studio.

From streaming platforms that provide global reach to independent artists, to free DAWs like BandLab, tech has revolutionized the way we discover, consume, and engage with music. 🎧🌍

Creators are harnessing the power of tech, breaking geographical boundaries and giving a platform to underrepresented genres and cultures. And, we’re just seeing the beginning. 💫🎵

See you in Belgium!

“What is your essential contribution?” This was the profound question posed at @reeperbahn_festival, where I had the privilege of leading a @keychangeeu workshop with @madamegandhi.

It wasn’t just a workshop - it was a challenge to identify our individual purposes and translate them into actionable steps to create a more diverse music industry.

Think about this for yourself. What is your essential contribution? What makes your friends and family light up? What energizes you? And how do you harness the clarity and discipline to use that essential contribution to create a better world?

Ask yourself, in a world filled with noise, what unique melody to you bring?

This day, this exercise, left me feeling inspired by all of the strong voices in the room who are putting in the work for the next generation in music to have a more equitable path. To all the artists and leaders who envision a brighter, diverse musical landscape - this journey is ours to shape. 🎧💪💕

#keychange #reeperbahn #reeperbahnfestival #changeyourmindset
